dismissalComment.html: madness! dismissalText.commentary: Sachin Tendulkar b Tshabalala 93 (106b 13x4 2x6 140m) SR: 87.73

Having been kept quite for four deliveries, he makes room to dab a tossed-up delivery, but loses the plot as the ball turns in sharply and takes the inside-edge onto middle and off...Tendulkar falls in the 90s for the second consecutive match and yet again a rookie spinner has his number

commentPreTextItems.html: Last over, just 1 to win...its the captain to bowl

commentTextItems.html: wide delivery outside off stump, Karthik coolly places that past a diving gully and steals the winning runs as India level the Future Cup with one to play!

commentPostTextItems.html: Thats that then, India winning by six wickets in the final over. They won the toss, put South Africa in to bat under overcast conditions, kept them to 225 for 6, and chased it down. Tendulkar led the way with his innings-filled 93, in the process crossing 15,000 ODI runs, and he was well supported in an opening stand of 134 by Ganguly (42). After a brief wobble, Yuvraj and Karthik held fort to clinch the deal with five deliveries to spare.
The series is now even on 1-1 with one game left, thats coming up in a couple days time.
India were under pressure to notch up a win here, and they did that, though not without a fight from South Africa.
Tendulkar picks up the Man of the Match award for his innings of 93, and he pockets US$1000.

Thats all we have for you, folks, and I hope you've enjoyed this game as much as I have. Do join us for the final game at 9.45GMT on Sunday, July 1. This is Jamie Alter, your commentator for the day, signing off. Cheers!

dismissalText.commentary: AB de Villiers run out (Singh/Dravid) 0 (6b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: madness! Short of a length on leg stump, van Wyk works it to square leg, no one's there and de Villiers calls for the run, RP does the fielding himself and van Wyk sends his partner back, bowler fires in a throw back to Dravid, who disturbs the bails but replays show de Villiers' bat was just in the air after he dived full stretch
